
'''= indie-film coop in San Francisco'''


URL = http://www.scarycow.com/


=Description=

"Scary Cow is a community-based & community-financed movie production company.

The idea is simple. Instead of paying your cable company a monthly fee to waste your life, take that money and invest it into your dream of being more involved in making feature films.

Meet and work with local filmmakers of all levels.

Scary Cow will connect you with other filmmakers to work on projects as a team. By connecting with other filmmakers in San Francisco you'll be making great local contacts - which is what this industry is all about!

What IS the Scary Cow model?

It's a film co-op. Members of Scary Cow will form into small teams. Those teams will compete to prove that they have what it takes to move to the next level. If the other members decide the project you worked on is one of the best, Scary Cow will give your team a budget to help finance your next project. Continue to create outstanding films, and you'll continue to receive a budget from Scary Cow to fund it! You learn to make films by actually making films!"
(http://www.scarycow.com/what.html)


